## **How It Works (Simple Example)**

### **Scenario: Backend Specialist Gets Slow**

```
10:00 AM - Agent executes 100 tasks
          ↓ Reports: avg_duration = 5.2 seconds

10:01 AM - Metrics Engine detects: duration > 5s threshold
          ↓ Triggers alert: "Performance degradation"

10:05 AM - Improvement Detector analyzes agent
          ↓ Proposes: "Add caching + reduce model size"
          ↓ Expected impact: -40% latency
          ↓ Risk level: LOW (auto-approve)

10:06 AM - A/B Test starts (300 second test)
          ↓ Control group (2 agents): normal execution
          ↓ Test group (agent): with caching + model change

10:11 AM - Test results analyzed
          ↓ Test group: 2.5 seconds/task (52% faster!)
          ↓ Control group: 5.1 seconds/task
          ↓ p-value: 0.012 (statistically significant)
          ↓ Improvement approved! ✅

10:12 AM - Rollout to all agents
          ↓ All agents now 50% faster

10:13 AM - Update agent profile
          ↓ Agent's skill "Task Execution" proficiency: advanced
          ↓ Task speed: +50% improvement recorded

User Impact: **ZERO INTERVENTION. System self-optimized.**
```

